review: Very good quality food and very good, pleasing service. Recommend the north-indian thali, but otherwise the paneer butter masala is to to die for! Would come back any time anf recommend the restaurant for business, family or couples..

A classy place, an extra ordinary menu and a wonderful presentation. It's rarely found but at TWIN'S you will, the cafe has everything you were looking for. It's an absolutely wonderful place, the taste is phenomenal which is a complete package with the presentation of food
The chicken Briyani was too hot and spicey was not able to have more than a spoon . I was happy by what all I got along with the briyani . Galubjamun was nice
The chapati that I got was thick and very raw . I Was not able to chew it at all . The chicken gravy had too much of oil . The butter milk and the full meal was good as a lunch for one person
